<LegalWrapper 
  title="Personal Data Processing Policy (PDPP)" 
  lastUpdated="April 2, 2026" 
  pdfLink="/docs/en/privacy-policy.pdf"
>
  <p class="text-xl font-500 mb-10 text-cnv-core">
    In compliance with current data protection regulations, <strong>CONNECTED NUTRITION VENTURES S.A.S.</strong> presents its policy for the handling of personal information.
  </p>

  <details>
    <summary>1. Identification of the Data Controller</summary>
    <div>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Corporate Name:</strong> CONNECTED NUTRITION VENTURES S.A.S.</li>
        <li><strong>NIT (Tax ID):</strong> 902045562</li>
        <li><strong>Domicile:</strong> Medellin, Colombia</li>
        <li><strong>Contact Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:protecciondatos@cnvsystem.com">protecciondatos@cnvsystem.com</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>2. Regulatory Framework</summary>
    <div>
      <p>This policy is governed by Law 1581 of 2012 and Decree 1074 of 2015 of the Republic of Colombia, as well as good practices and international standards regarding personal data protection.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>3. Guiding Principles</summary>
    <div>
      <p>CNV will harmoniously and integrally apply the following principles: Legality, Purpose, Freedom, Truthfulness or Quality, Transparency, Access and Restricted Circulation, Security, and Confidentiality.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>4. Key Definitions</summary>
    <div>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Personal Data:</strong> Any information linked or that can be associated with one or several determined or determinable natural persons.</li>
        <li><strong>Data Subject:</strong> Natural person whose personal data is subject to Processing.</li>
        <li><strong>Processing:</strong> Any operation or set of operations on personal data.</li>
        <li><strong>Data Processor:</strong> Person or entity that performs the Processing of data on behalf of the Data Controller.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>5. Purposes of Processing</summary>
    <div>
      <p>The personal data collected through our digital channels will be used strictly to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Manage and respond to contact requests and user requirements.</li>
        <li>Send institutional, commercial, or technical information related to the request made by the data subject or with CNV services, when authorized.</li>
        <li>Improve the user experience on the website through statistical analysis of interaction.</li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations and internal audits.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>6. International Data Transfer and Transmission</summary>
    <div>
      <p>To ensure the technical operation of the website, processing may involve the international transmission or transfer of personal data to technological providers, including, among others, hosting services, web analytics, email delivery, and computer security. Such transfer or transmission will be previously authorized by the data subject through the consent mechanisms provided on the website, ensuring that third parties comply with confidentiality obligations and adequate information protection standards.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>7. Rights of the Data Subject</summary>
    <div>
      <p>As the data subject, you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Know, update, and rectify your personal data before CNV.</li>
        <li>Request proof of the authorization granted.</li>
        <li>Be informed by CNV, upon request, regarding the use given to your data.</li>
        <li>Revoke the authorization and/or request the deletion of the data when legal principles are not respected.</li>
        <li>File complaints with the Superintendence of Industry and Commerce (SIC) in Colombia.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>8. Procedure for Exercising Rights</summary>
    <div>
      <p>Inquiries and claims must be sent via written request to the email: <a href="mailto:protecciondatos@cnvsystem.com">protecciondatos@cnvsystem.com</a>.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Inquiries:</strong> Will be addressed within a maximum of ten (10) business days.</li>
        <li><strong>Claims:</strong> Will be addressed within a maximum of fifteen (15) business days.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>9. Information Security</summary>
    <div>
      <p>CNV implements reasonable technical, administrative, and organizational measures to protect personal data. Access to information is restricted to authorized personnel through authentication controls, role-based access management, and activity logging.</p>
    </div>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>10. Validity</summary>
    <div>
      <p>This policy becomes effective upon publication. Personal data will be processed for the time necessary to fulfill the described purposes, as long as a legal or contractual obligation requires it, and/or until the data subject requests its deletion when legally applicable.</p>
    </div>
  </details>
</LegalWrapper>